        <div class="section">
            <h3>How this fits inside the broader argument</h3>

            <p class="prose">The bitcoin-backed mortgage is one specific use case inside the broader question the <a href="/borrowing-against-your-stack.html">Borrowing Against Your Stack</a> page exists to answer. It happens to be the one where the structural argument lands cleanest, because the product itself eliminates the margin-call risk that defined CeFi&rsquo;s force-liquidation failure mode &mdash; the single feature most likely to put a healthy bitcoin-backed borrower in distress.</p>

            <p class="prose">The full hierarchy of bitcoin-backed lending categories sits on that broader page. Mortgages sit on the &ldquo;serious consideration&rdquo; tier alongside collaborative-custody multisig and Tier-1 non-rehypothecating CeFi &mdash; with the distinguishing feature that this is the only category in which <strong>a 30-year duration and a 60-day-not-60-minutes liquidation buffer apply to bitcoin collateral simultaneously</strong>. For the specific use case of funding a primary-residence purchase against an appreciated bitcoin stack, that combination is difficult to beat.</p>

            <p class="prose">As with the rest of the site, the right reading isn&rsquo;t &ldquo;this is the answer.&rdquo; The right reading is: <em>here&rsquo;s the structural detail you need to evaluate whether it&rsquo;s the answer for your specific situation</em>. If the structural fit lines up, this is the cleanest version of the borrow-against-bitcoin approach currently available in the US regulated tier for funding a home purchase. If it doesn&rsquo;t, the page has done its job by helping you walk away on reflection rather than sleepwalking in.</p>
